cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about Chinese word segmentation, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel shared Bi-LSTM-CRF model, which is a type of neural network, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper leverages multiple character embeddings, which are a type of feature engineering, suggesting that it could also fit into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also conducts experiments and reports F1 scores, indicating that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with text data and proposes a method for improving performance, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
